3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* match_list 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* generic list-based pattern matching
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <match_list.h>
10/*
11/* MATCH_LIST *match_list_init(pname, flags, pattern_list, count, func,...)
12/* const char *pname;
13/* int flags;
14/* const char *pattern_list;
15/* int count;
16/* int (*func)(int flags, const char *string, const char *pattern);
17/*
18/* int match_list_match(list, string,...)
19/* MATCH_LIST *list;
20/* const char *string;
21/*
22/* void match_list_free(list)
23/* MATCH_LIST *list;
24/* DESCRIPTION
25/* This module implements a framework for tests for list
26/* membership. The actual tests are done by user-supplied
27/* functions.
28/*
29/* Patterns are separated by whitespace and/or commas. A pattern
30/* is either a string, a file name (in which case the contents
31/* of the file are substituted for the file name) or a type:name
32/* lookup table specification. In order to reverse the result
33/* of a pattern match, precede a pattern with an exclamation
34/* point (!).
35/*
36/* match_list_init() performs initializations. When the global
37/* util_utf8_enable variable is non-zero, and when the code
38/* is compiled with EAI support, string comparison will use
39/* caseless UTF-8 mode. Otherwise, only ASCII characters will
40/* be casefolded.
41/*
42/* match_list_match() matches strings against the specified
43/* pattern list, passing the first string to the first function
44/* given to match_list_init(), the second string to the second
45/* function, and so on.
46/*
47/* match_list_free() releases storage allocated by match_list_init().
48/*
49/* Arguments:
50/* .IP pname
51/* Parameter name or other identifying information that is
52/* prepended to error messages.
53/* .IP flags
54/* Specifies the bit-wise OR of zero or more of the following:
55/* .RS
56/* .IP MATCH_FLAG_PARENT
57/* The hostname pattern foo.com matches any name within the
58/* domain foo.com. If this flag is cleared, foo.com matches
59/* itself only, and .foo.com matches any name below the domain
60/* foo.com.
61/* .IP MATCH_FLAG_RETURN
62/* Request that match_list_match() logs a warning and returns
63/* zero (with list->error set to a non-zero dictionary error
64/* code) instead of raising a fatal run-time error.
65/* .RE
66/* Specify MATCH_FLAG_NONE to request none of the above.
67/* .IP pattern_list
68/* A list of patterns.
69/* .IP count
70/* Specifies how many match functions follow.
71/* .IP list
72/* Pattern list produced by match_list_init().
73/* .IP string
74/* Search string.
75/* DIAGNOSTICS
76/* Fatal error: unable to open or read a match_list file; invalid
77/* match_list pattern; casefold error (UTF-8 mode only).
78/* SEE ALSO
79/* host_match(3) match hosts by name or by address
80/* LICENSE
81/* .ad
82/* .fi
83/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
84/* AUTHOR(S)
85/* Wietse Venema
86/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
87/* P.O. Box 704
88/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
89/*--*/
90

112/* Application-specific */
113
114#define MATCH_DICTIONARY(pattern) \
115 ((pattern)[0] != '[' && strchr((pattern), ':') != 0)
116
117/* match_list_parse - parse buffer, destroy buffer */
118
119static ARGV *match_list_parse(MATCH_LIST *match_list, ARGV *pat_list,
120 char *string, int init_match)
121{
122 const char *myname = "match_list_parse";
123 VSTRING *buf = vstring_alloc(10);
124 VSTREAM *fp;
125 const char *delim = CHARS_COMMA_SP;
126 char *bp = string;
127 char *start;
128 char *item;
129 char *map_type_name_flags;
130 int match;
131
132 /*
133 * We do not use DICT_FLAG_FOLD_FIX, because we casefold the search
134 * string at the beginning of a search, and we use strcmp() for string
135 * comparison. This works because string patterns are casefolded during
136 * match_list initialization, and databases are supposed to fold case
137 * upon creation.
138 */
139#define OPEN_FLAGS O_RDONLY
140#define DICT_FLAGS (DICT_FLAG_LOCK | DICT_FLAG_UTF8_REQUEST)
141#define STR(x) vstring_str(x)
142
143 /*
144 * /filename contents are expanded in-line. To support !/filename we
145 * prepend the negation operator to each item from the file.
146 *
147 * If there is an error, implement graceful degradation by inserting a
148 * pseudo table whose lookups fail with a warning message.
149 */
150 while ((start = mystrtokq(&bp, delim, CHARS_BRACE)) != 0) {
151 if (*start == '#') {
152 msg_warn("%s: comment at end of line is not supported: %s %s",
153 match_list->pname, start, bp);
154 break;
155 }
156 for (match = init_match, item = start; *item == '!'; item++)
157 match = !match;
158 if (*item == 0)
159 /* No graceful degradation for this... */
160 msg_fatal("%s: no pattern after '!'", match_list->pname);
161 if (*item == '/') { /* /file/name */
162 if ((fp = vstream_fopen(item, O_RDONLY, 0)) == 0) {
163 /* Replace unusable pattern with pseudo table. */
164 vstring_sprintf(buf, "%s:%s", DICT_TYPE_NOFILE, item);
165 if (dict_handle(STR(buf)) == 0)
166 dict_register(STR(buf),
167 dict_surrogate(DICT_TYPE_NOFILE, item,
168 OPEN_FLAGS, DICT_FLAGS,
169 "open file %s: %m", item));
170 argv_add(pat_list, STR(buf), (char *) 0);
171 } else {
172 while (vstring_fgets(buf, fp))
173 if (vstring_str(buf)[0] != '#')
174 pat_list = match_list_parse(match_list, pat_list,
175 vstring_str(buf), match);
176 if (vstream_fclose(fp))
177 msg_fatal("%s: read file %s: %m", myname, item);
178 }
179 } else if (MATCH_DICTIONARY(item)) { /* type:table */
180 vstring_sprintf(buf, "%s%s(%o,%s)", match ? "" : "!",
181 item, OPEN_FLAGS, dict_flags_str(DICT_FLAGS));
182 map_type_name_flags = STR(buf) + (match == 0);
183 if (dict_handle(map_type_name_flags) == 0)
184 dict_register(map_type_name_flags,
185 dict_open(item, OPEN_FLAGS, DICT_FLAGS));
186 argv_add(pat_list, STR(buf), (char *) 0);
187 } else { /* other pattern */
188 casefold(match_list->fold_buf, match ?
189 item : STR(vstring_sprintf(buf, "!%s", item)));
190 argv_add(pat_list, STR(match_list->fold_buf), (char *) 0);
191 }
192 }
193 vstring_free(buf);
194 return (pat_list);
195}
196
197/* match_list_init - initialize pattern list */
198
199MATCH_LIST *match_list_init(const char *pname, int flags,
200 const char *patterns, int match_count,...)
201{
202 MATCH_LIST *list;
203 char *saved_patterns;
204 va_list ap;
205 int i;
206
207 if (flags & ~MATCH_FLAG_ALL)
208 msg_panic("match_list_init: bad flags 0x%x", flags);
209
210 list = (MATCH_LIST *) mymalloc(sizeof(*list));
211 list->pname = mystrdup(pname);
212 list->flags = flags;
213 list->match_count = match_count;
214 list->match_func =
215 (MATCH_LIST_FN *) mymalloc(match_count * sizeof(MATCH_LIST_FN));
216 list->match_args =
217 (const char **) mymalloc(match_count * sizeof(const char *));
218 va_start(ap, match_count);
219 for (i = 0; i < match_count; i++)
220 list->match_func[i] = va_arg(ap, MATCH_LIST_FN);
221 va_end(ap);
222 list->error = 0;
223 list->fold_buf = vstring_alloc(20);
224
225#define DO_MATCH 1
226
227 saved_patterns = mystrdup(patterns);
228 list->patterns = match_list_parse(list, argv_alloc(1), saved_patterns,
229 DO_MATCH);
230 argv_terminate(list->patterns);
231 myfree(saved_patterns);
232 return (list);
233}
234
235/* match_list_match - match strings against pattern list */
236
237int match_list_match(MATCH_LIST *list,...)
238{
239 const char *myname = "match_list_match";
240 char **cpp;
241 char *pat;
242 int match;
243 int i;
244 va_list ap;
245
246 /*
247 * Iterate over all patterns in the list, stop at the first match.
248 */
249 va_start(ap, list);
250 for (i = 0; i < list->match_count; i++)
251 list->match_args[i] = va_arg(ap, const char *);
252 va_end(ap);
253
254 list->error = 0;
255 for (cpp = list->patterns->argv; (pat = *cpp) != 0; cpp++) {
256 for (match = 1; *pat == '!'; pat++)
257 match = !match;
258 for (i = 0; i < list->match_count; i++) {
259 casefold(list->fold_buf, list->match_args[i]);
260 if (list->match_func[i] (list, STR(list->fold_buf), pat))
261 return (match);
262 else if (list->error != 0)
263 return (0);
264 }
265 }
266 if (msg_verbose)
267 for (i = 0; i < list->match_count; i++)
268 msg_info("%s: %s: no match", myname, list->match_args[i]);
269 return (0);
270}
271
272/* match_list_free - release storage */
273
274void match_list_free(MATCH_LIST *list)
275{
276 /* XXX Should decrement map refcounts. */
277 myfree(list->pname);
278 argv_free(list->patterns);
279 myfree((void *) list->match_func);
280 myfree((void *) list->match_args);
281 vstring_free(list->fold_buf);
282 myfree((void *) list);
283}
